  "text": "). As discussed in [CITATION_1] in this case by qFK we obtain the flag manifold Z = F 1,n (C n+2 ) which is the twistor space of the Grassmannian Gr 2 (C n+2 ). By Remark 5.1, Z is the gluing of of two trivial rank n + 1 bundles using the blow downs from O(−1, 0) and O(0, −1) respectively and the canonical triviality of O( Indeed, let C n+2 with standard coordinates (p, q 0 , . . . , q n ) be equipped with standard hermitian product and the C × -action (λ −1 p, λq 0 , . . . λq n ) and denote by a the line defined by the equation q 0 = · · · = q n = 0. Then the real structure on Z is defined by ⊥ and the C × -action on C n+2 induce a C × -action on Z fixing two ⊥-conjugated submanifolds of Z isomorphic to CP n namely {(l, K) ∈ F 1,n (C n+2 ) : l = a} and {(l, K) ∈ F 1,n (C n+2 ) : K = a ⊥ }. The C × -action defines fibrations and vector bundle structures on {(l, K) ∈ F 1,n (C n+2 ) : l ∩ a ⊥ = 0} and {(l, K) ∈ F 1,n (C n+2 ) : K ∩ a = 0} such that the action is the scalar multiplication in the fibres and its inverse respectively. Consider (l, K) ∈ F 1,n (C n+2 ) such that l ∩ a ⊥ = 0 and set k = K ⊥ . Let us write l = span(P +Q) and k = span(P +Q) forP ,P ∈ a,Q,Q ∈ a ⊥ andP ,Q = 0; without loss of generality we can fixP to be defined by p = 1. Then the action of an element λ ∈ C × on (l, K)",
